The paper deals with obstacle representations of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also involves the computation of visibility graphs (cs.DS) and the complexity of graph problems (cs.CC). The use of graphs and their properties suggests that it may also fall under discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT).
